{"id":"03trbq7o","parent_id":"2evkv6xf","name":"Phase 4.1 — Shell-owned render camera (unify offline + online chase camera)","description":"Consolidation follow-up (after l2mowwvj). Today the offline and online drivers EACH create their own plain chase camera (createChaseCamera, look-ahead off) and overwrite the rendered camera after flyByWire.updateCamera, while flyByWire ALSO owns an internal chase camera (with cursor look-ahead) used for the controlUp steering reference + death-cam blend. That is three chase-camera instances and a duplicated 'overwrite the view with a plain chase camera' pattern across the two drivers, plus a wasted flyByWire render each frame. Hoist ONE plain render chase camera into the shell (createClientShell), owned and applied by the shell each frame, so both drivers share it. Reduce flyByWire's internal chase camera to just the controlUp/aim steering reference and the death-cam blend; it should stop driving the rendered camera. Do this before Phase 5 builds more camera/HUD onto the shell. Polish, not urgent: current code works (the online held-cursor view waver was fixed by giving the online driver its own plain render camera in commit 9f80f1b).","priority":2,"completed":true,"result":"Hoisted the per-driver flying chase camera into the shell as one shared render camera. clientShell now owns a createChaseCamera() instance exposed via snapRenderCamera(target) + updateRenderCamera(target, dt); offlineDriver and onlineDriver call those instead of each owning a plain chase camera (removed their createChaseCamera + chaseCamera.ts imports). Fly-by-wire keeps its internal chase camera for the look-ahead-free controlUp steering reference and for rendering the death-cam blend + spectate view (offline) — intentionally untouched. Behavior-preserving: online held-cursor waver fix preserved (shell camera is look-ahead-free), offline flying view identical, spectate/death-cam path unchanged. Verified camera ordering (render camera reads the clean pose before the mesh-only rotation-offset premultiply). Shipped in PR #37 (draft), commit 3d7c961; vp check + 287 tests + fallow all green.","metadata":{"commit":{"sha":"3d7c961","message":":recycle: Shell-owned render camera + offline boot-failure cleanup","branch":"refactor/shell-render-camera","timestamp":"2026-06-30T04:39:40.929Z"}},"created_at":"2026-06-30T01:13:41.665Z","updated_at":"2026-06-30T04:39:40.933Z","started_at":"2026-06-30T03:49:47.841Z","completed_at":"2026-06-30T04:39:40.933Z","blockedBy":["l2mowwvj"],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
