{"id":"0m493lgo","parent_id":null,"name":"Scriptlancer — Freelancer-style browser space flight game","description":"A web-based 3D space flight/combat game inspired by Freelancer and Librelancer, built with three.js and the Vite+ toolchain (TypeScript, Bun).\n\nArchitecture & conventions:\n- All scene/render logic under src/game/; three.js kept out of the Preact UI layer.\n- Pure, unit-tested math & physics modules (src/game/math, src/game/physics, src/game/control, src/game/controls) with thin effectful shells tagged @sideEffect. See AGENTS.md.\n- Deliberately decoupled systems: fly-by-wire mouse steering (flyByWire.ts) + PID controllers, a Librelancer-ported chase camera (chaseCamera.ts), ship angular dynamics (shipSteering.ts), linear thrust (shipThrust.ts), HUD reticle (reticleHud.ts).\n\nCurrent state:\n- Mouse/touch fly-by-wire steering, PID pitch/yaw/roll with bank-into-turn.\n- Chase camera using position = ship + R*offset with smoothing/turn-lead.\n- Always-on forward thrust (drag-limited top speed; W-throttle is a later step).\n- Aim cone centered on the ship forward axis (centered cursor = straight flight); HUD shows a movable diamond steering reticle plus a static center boresight marker.\n\nNorth star: Freelancer and Librelancer are the dream/reference for game feel, especially flight and targeting.\n\nRoadmap (umbrella): combat (projectiles + aiming), targets/enemies & hit detection, throttle controls, thruster/weapon VFX, Freelancer-style units pass, HUD expansion.","priority":1,"completed":false,"result":null,"metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-21T16:56:46.002Z","updated_at":"2026-06-21T16:56:46.002Z","started_at":null,"completed_at":null,"blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":["jke0r8bn","opo6ygoq","qnbk384g","bcohudeg","20au5fho","q6t535u3","dwnl8omw","rmuexegj","wtysthix","hl9qg145","lsidb0yp","xgfkvvrt","2evkv6xf","wmozjx6s","xw3fys60","27bj688a"]}
