{"id":"31gfijwz","parent_id":"2evkv6xf","name":"Phase 3 — Client-side prediction + reconciliation (local ship)","description":"CONTEXT: Removes input lag on the player own ship. One of the two trickiest phases — expect iteration, and expect the user to verify FEEL (this gate is not unit-testable).\n\nINVESTIGATE: local input history buffer keyed by tick; applying input immediately to the local ship; on each authoritative snapshot, snap to server state then REPLAY unacked inputs; SMOOTH the residual error over several frames (no snapping); sequence numbers / server-ack of last processed input.\n\nENGAGE THE USER FIRST: before implementing, agree the approach with the user (especially error-smoothing behavior). Then implement, and hand BACK to the user to play-test the feel — do NOT self-mark done.\n\nOPEN QUESTIONS FOR THE USER: error-smoothing curve and threshold (when to snap vs blend); how to handle prediction of collisions the server resolves differently.\n\nREFERENCES (implement the standard pattern, do not invent one): Gabriel Gambetta \"Fast-Paced Multiplayer\" — Client-Side Prediction and Server Reconciliation https://www.gabrielgambetta.com/client-server-game-architecture.html ; Glenn Fiedler networked physics https://gafferongames.com/categories/networked-physics/\n\nDONE WHEN: local ship has zero perceived input lag and corrections are visually imperceptible in normal play. NOTE: implement, then hand back to the user to verify the feel gate — do not self-mark done.\n\nSTATUS (2026-06-29): Implemented in PR #34 (branch roll-damping-fix) and feel-confirmed by the user (kill-cam working, corrections imperceptible). Local input history with immediate apply, snap-to-server then replay-unacked, render-side residual error smoothing (position lerp plus rotation slerp), and a server per-player input queue so reconciliation stays clean. Extras also landed: cursor-decoupled reticle, smoothed lead indicator, and the shared-sim offline consolidation. Not yet merged; pending CodeRabbit and merge. Per the do-not-self-mark-done instruction above, left for the user to mark done on merge.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Client-side prediction + reconciliation shipped in PR #34, feel-confirmed: local input history with immediate apply, snap-to-server then replay-unacked, render-side residual error smoothing (position lerp + rotation slerp), server per-player input queue. Extras: cursor-decoupled reticle, smoothed lead indicator, shared-sim offline consolidation, GLB-derived asteroid colliders, combat parity.","metadata":{"commit":{"sha":"c3f3422","message":":sparkles: Phase 3 netcode + shared-sim offline consolidation","branch":"roll-damping-fix","timestamp":"2026-06-29T21:56:10.314Z"}},"created_at":"2026-06-26T08:41:06.572Z","updated_at":"2026-06-29T21:56:10.318Z","started_at":"2026-06-28T06:07:31.814Z","completed_at":"2026-06-29T21:56:10.318Z","blockedBy":["5fn4vdf4"],"blocks":["l2mowwvj"],"children":[]}
{"id":"3cc9jmf0","parent_id":"zgbnfktr","name":"Blog: rebuilding greglinscheid.com","description":"Write a blog post for greglinscheid.com about rebuilding this repo — crisp, fun, informative (a blog read, not a technical doc). Include code blocks and links where they help.\n\n## Prerequisite\n\nComplete **lbyqyqsy** (Migrate content from astro-greg) first so the post can reference the real migrated stack, not plans.\n\n## Suggested slug / file\n\n`src/content/blog/rebuilding-greglinscheid-com.md` (or similar — pick a slug that reads well in the URL)\n\n## Narrative arc\n\n1. **Where it started** — [astro-greg](https://github.com/Vilos92/astro-greg) shipped June 2024 (first commit **2024-06-28**; hello-world `pubDate` June 29 2024). Astro 5, Tailwind 3 + typography plugin, React island for breadcrumbs, MDX, content collections, Prettier/ESLint/husky.\n\n2. **Life got busier** — Since then: marriage, travel, work. Less free time for side projects. The old site sat fine; the *stack* aged.\n\n3. **The world changed** — LLMs are daily at work now. That shifts how you build (and how much boilerplate you tolerate).\n\n4. **New toolchain appetite** — Vite+, Cloudflare patterns from other repos, Bun-first scripts, Oxlint/Oxfmt via `vp`. This rebuild is adapting the personal site to those habits.\n\n5. **Back to real CSS** — Trending away from Tailwind (especially with LLM help writing CSS). This site uses **Vanilla Extract** (`*.css.ts`), design tokens in `src/styles/tokens.ts`, Fraunces + Source Sans 3, warm paper palette. Brief contrast with astro-greg Tailwind — not a Tailwind hit piece, just why VE + tokens felt right here. Maybe a small `tokens.ts` or `prose.css.ts` snippet.\n\n## Fallow section (important — agentic development angle)\n\nExplain **fallow** as a guardrail for agent-written code: dead-code, dupes, complexity/health, dependency hygiene. Not ESLint — complementary.\n\n**gdex example to cite** (local: `/Users/greg.linscheid/greg_projects/gdex`):\n- **078eab4** (`:shirt: fallow base`) — intentionally committed *empty* `.fallow/dupes-baseline.json` and `.fallow/health-baseline.json` so `fallow audit` could gate **new** findings on changed files without blocking the whole repo on day-one inherited debt.\n- **7abf7ab** (`:shirt: fallow`) — when keyboard-nav work touched `TaskList` tests, audit flagged duplicate fixture data across `taskListNavigation.test.ts` and `taskLevel.test.ts`. **Fix:** extract shared `src/lib/sampleTasks.fixture.ts` — *not* expand the baseline. Good story: baseline enables adoption; fixes are still required when you touch the code.\n- **1d4dae6** (`fallow - TaskBreadcrumb`) — health/complexity: extract `toBreadcrumbSegment` helper instead of ignoring complexity warnings.\n\nOptional one-liner contrast: grynthia **ej3ssg1c** grandfathered 9 dup clone groups in a baseline when dedup was deferred — different tradeoff, same tool.\n\nLink: https://github.com/fallow-rs/fallow\n\nTone: baselines are a deliberate human decision (see AGENTS.md — ask before saving), not a way to greenwash agent slop.\n\n## Stack / tooling section\n\nTable (markdown) of the quality gate — one row each, short description; fallow row can point to section above.\n\n| Tool | Command | What it does |\n|------|---------|--------------|\n| Vite+ / `vp` | `vp check` | Oxfmt + Oxlint + typecheck bundle |\n| Oxfmt | `bun run fmt:check` | Format |\n| Oxlint | `bun run lint` | Lint |\n| TypeScript | `bun run typecheck` | `tsc --noEmit` |\n| Vitest (via Vite+) | `bun run test` | Unit tests |\n| Fallow | `bun run fallow:audit` | Audit changed files vs baselines |\n| Astro | `bun run build` | Static site build |\n\nCI: `.github/workflows/continuous-integration.yaml` — fmt, lint, typecheck, test, fallow (fetch-depth 0 for merge base).\n\nEntry surface for fallow: `src/site.ts` + `.fallowrc.jsonc`.\n\n## Links worth including\n\n- astro-greg: https://github.com/Vilos92/astro-greg\n- Vite+: https://viteplus.dev/guide/\n- Vanilla Extract: https://vanilla-extract.style/\n- fallow: https://github.com/fallow-rs/fallow\n- gdex (sibling pattern): https://github.com/Vilos92/gdex (if public)\n\n## Done when\n\n- New post in `src/content/blog/` with frontmatter (`title`, `description`, `pubDate`, etc.)\n- Reads well on the live prose styles (`Prose.astro` / `prose.css.ts`)\n- `vp check`, `bun run test`, `bun run fallow:audit`, `bun run build` pass\n- Greg has reviewed tone and any personal details before publish","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Added rebuilding-greglinscheid-com blog post (technical skeleton + Greg placeholders), Milo hero image, hello-world cross-link; latest entry auto-updates via pubDate; vp check/test/fallow/build pass.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-07T16:56:22.221Z","updated_at":"2026-06-07T17:19:29.985Z","started_at":"2026-06-07T16:57:14.840Z","completed_at":"2026-06-07T17:19:29.985Z","blockedBy":["lbyqyqsy"],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
