{"id":"4dgaqbbb","parent_id":"ia40wzb6","name":"macOS release workflow (GitHub Releases)","description":"GOAL\nAdd `.github/workflows/release-macos.yaml` that builds the Tauri app for Apple Silicon and attaches bundles to a GitHub Release — not on every push to main (macOS minutes are expensive).\n\nTRIGGER (pick one clear model, document in the workflow header)\nPrefer the GitHub Releases UI flow:\n- `on.release.types: [published]` — run when a release is published (tag already exists).\n- Checkout `github.event.release.tag_name` so the build matches what was released.\n- Upload with `tauri-apps/tauri-action` using `releaseId: ${{ github.event.release.id }}` (attach assets to the release the user created; do not create a competing release from scratch unless we document why).\n\nOptional: `workflow_dispatch` for a packaging smoke build (artifacts only, no release row).\n\nDo NOT wire `push.branches: [main]` for full macOS bundles — too costly for routine merges. CI already covers main on Linux.\n\nBUILD\n- `runs-on: macos-latest`, `args: --target aarch64-apple-darwin`\n- `tauriScript: bun run tauri` (project CLI, not global)\n- Reuse composite actions: `install-rust` (cache on), `install-bun-and-dependencies`\n- `rustup target add aarch64-apple-darwin` (explicit target, predictable bundle paths)\n- Unsigned for now; comment points at https://v2.tauri.app/distribute/sign/macos/ and APPLE_* secrets for later\n\nHOUSE STYLE\n- Pin actions by SHA (match `continuous-integration.yaml`)\n- Comments: why over what, Greg tone (short, no semicolon chains) — see recent workflow comment pass on the deleted file for vibe\n- `permissions.contents: write` only on the job that talks to Releases API\n- `concurrency` per ref, `cancel-in-progress: false` (avoid half-uploaded releases)\n\nACCEPTANCE\n- Publishing a GitHub Release (with a `v*` tag) runs the workflow and attaches `.dmg` / macOS bundle assets to that release\n- No macOS release workflow on ordinary merges to main\n- `workflow_dispatch` still works for manual artifact checks\n- Workflow file deleted in resizable-pane branch — this task reintroduces it with the strategy above","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Shipped via PR #20 (builds). .github/workflows/builds.yaml builds the Tauri app and attaches bundles to GitHub Releases. Subsequent fixes landed in 84714fb (build fix) and f6a0017 (macOS dmg fix). Follow-up: app icon for the built binary is tracked separately.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-01T09:05:54.213Z","updated_at":"2026-06-02T15:41:07.786Z","started_at":"2026-06-02T15:41:07.785Z","completed_at":"2026-06-02T15:41:07.786Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
