{"id":"5fn4vdf4","parent_id":"2evkv6xf","name":"Phase 2.5 — Client rewire: consume shared sim (offline in-process), drop legacy duplicate","description":"Make the client consume packages/shared as the single sim, eliminating the temporary duplication left by Phase 1.\n\nCONTEXT: Phase 1 extracted the authoritative sim into packages/shared and proved it runs headless (Bun) AND in the browser. But the client still runs its LEGACY three.js sim (apps/client/src/game/physics/createPhysicsWorld.ts, shipDynamics.ts, shipSteering.ts, shipThrust.ts, pilot/createAiPilot.ts + avoidance/pursuit/combat, weapon/weaponSystem.ts, aiWeaponSystem.ts, projectile motion, collisionGeometry.ts, ship/shipHealth.ts). That legacy sim DUPLICATES packages/shared and will drift.\n\nGOAL: delete the legacy client sim and have the client run packages/shared as the one codebase. OFFLINE = run the shared sim in-process in the browser (no separate server process — same module ticked locally; proven feasible by Phase 1's happy-dom browser determinism tests). ONLINE = render server snapshots (Phase 2) and, with Phase 3, predict using the same shared sim. Convert at the three boundary only: shared POJO Vec3/Quat <-> three Object3D position/quaternion for rendering; three/VFX/audio/HUD/camera/input-capture stay client.\n\nWHY: single source of truth (no client/server logic duplication — Greg's explicit concern); instant offline play that takes advantage of being a web game; and the required foundation for Phase 3 prediction (which can't run without the client ticking the shared sim locally).\n\nGATE: flight must feel identical to today — this swaps the sim implementation, not its behavior. Verify by play-test (human-in-the-loop), like the Phase 0 feel gate. Also fold in the dynamic-asteroid authoritative world if convenient (see Phase 2 note) so offline matches the real field.\n\nSEQUENCING: independent of Phase 2 (server-side), but BLOCKS Phase 3 (prediction). Surfaced during Phase 2 design.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Shared-sim offline mode landed (PR #32, merged to main). Client runs the shared authoritative singlePlayerWorld in-browser via ?sharedsim, rendering shared-sim state through the same path the networked client uses. Extracted worldAssembly shared by singlePlayerWorld/dogfightWorld; proved the shared sim is browser-runnable with faithful flight feel (the prediction substrate for Phase 3). Default single-player and networked modes intact. Remaining convergence — unify the client shell, move input capture into it, retire the parallel three-based sim — folds into Phase 3.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-27T19:25:02.426Z","updated_at":"2026-06-28T06:07:31.678Z","started_at":"2026-06-27T21:18:24.494Z","completed_at":"2026-06-28T06:07:31.678Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":["31gfijwz"],"children":[]}
