{"id":"7doslvmi","parent_id":"2evkv6xf","name":"Target-aware aim convergence (raycast cursor to the actual ship)","description":"COMBAT-FEEL FOLLOW-UP (surfaced during Phase 5 slice 5a feel-test, 2026-06-30). Today the aim point (flyByWire.getAimPoint -> ClientInput.aimPoint -> server weaponSystem) is placed at a FIXED depth (400 units) down the cursor ray. When the target is closer than 400u, the guns converge past it, so the muzzle->aimPoint line rides slightly above a closer ship sitting right under the reticle (fixed-convergence parallax). The player compensates by aiming a touch high. PROPER FIX: make aim target-aware — each tick raycast the cursor ray against the rendered ships (the client already holds the remote ship Object3Ds via networkShipRegistry; a three.js Raycaster against them works) and, if it hits one, set aimPoint at that real hit distance instead of the fixed 400; otherwise fall back to 400. Then bolts converge on whatever ship is under the reticle at any range. Feel-sensitive; deferred from 5a. INTERIM MITIGATION already in place: BOLT_HIT_RADIUS=2.0 (swept-sphere bolt hits) masks the parallax by catching off-line targets. Note: getAimPoint is shared with the offline auto-fire path, so consider both modes.","priority":3,"completed":true,"result":"Manual-lead aim in both modes: guns converge at the lead point's range so aligning the cursor with the lead indicator lands the shot. Online also got a lead indicator, per-enemy target indicators, and auto-fire. Feel-tested good.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-30T06:40:29.593Z","updated_at":"2026-06-30T07:34:26.971Z","started_at":"2026-06-30T06:43:33.930Z","completed_at":"2026-06-30T07:34:26.971Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
{"id":"877gahpp","parent_id":"ia40wzb6","name":"Quick prompts: polish copy button layout","description":"## Problem\n\nIn the inline Quick prompts code block (`AgentPromptCodeBlock`), long prompt text scrolls inside the `<pre>` while the copy button lives in a separate toolbar column to the right. When the scrollbar appears, there is an awkward empty vertical strip between the scrollbar and the copy button — the button column stretches full height but only the icon sits at the top.\n\nRelevant files:\n- `src/components/TaskDetail/QuickPrompts/AgentPromptCodeBlock.tsx`\n- `src/components/TaskDetail/QuickPrompts/taskDetailQuickPrompts.css.ts`\n\n## Reference: what GitHub does\n\nGitHub does **not** generally avoid scrollbars in code blocks — long content still scrolls. Their usual pattern is:\n\n- Copy control is **overlaid** in the top-right corner of the code block (absolute/float on the wrapper), not in a sibling column beside the scrollbar.\n- Button appears on hover/focus; it sits on the code block background, independent of scroll position.\n- Scrollbar stays on the content area only; the copy affordance does not compete for a second vertical lane.\n\nWorth comparing against GitHub’s markdown/PR code block chrome for layout inspiration (overlay vs side column).\n\n## Goals\n\n1. Remove the awkward scrollbar-adjacent dead space in the quick prompt code block.\n2. Keep copy feedback (clipboard icon → checkmark / “Copied!”) and keyboard `$mod+C` behavior unchanged.\n3. Prefer a solution that reads cleanly at ~5-line cap with and without overflow.\n\n## Ideas (pick one or hybrid)\n\n- **Overlay copy button** on the code block wrapper (top-right), GitHub-style.\n- **Single scroll container** wrapping both text + button so the toolbar scrolls with content (usually worse — likely skip).\n- **Scrollbar gutter / padding** adjustments if overlay feels too heavy — e.g. inset copy into padding-right of `<pre>` so scrollbar and button share one edge.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- No orphan vertical bar beside the scrollbar when prompt text overflows.\n- Copy button remains discoverable and accessible (title, aria-label, focus-visible).\n- Looks good in light and dark mode; no regression to `QuickPromptsPanel` / workspace home surfaces.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Overlay copy button on quick-prompt code block (GitHub-style); scrollbar gutter + decoupled padding so text clears button without a side column; AutoThemeIcon updated to crescent-with-rays.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-07T00:14:48.623Z","updated_at":"2026-06-07T04:52:48.041Z","started_at":"2026-06-07T00:35:22.633Z","completed_at":"2026-06-07T04:52:48.041Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
{"id":"9561xh4k","parent_id":"2evkv6xf","name":"Phase 1 — Extract shared sim core that runs headless under Bun","description":"CONTEXT: Need one authoritative simulation usable in browser AND on the Bun server. Lands in packages/shared (the workspace skeleton is created by Phase 0.5). This is the LOGIC extraction — kept separate from the mechanical move.\n\nINVESTIGATE: pulling the per-tick logic into a pure packages/shared sim core with signature roughly (state, inputs, TICK) => state, free of three.js/DOM; loading Rapier WASM under Bun vs browser; what state must be serializable; REWORK colliderFromObject.ts — the server has no three.js and must not ship GLB, so collision shapes move to shared collider/physics DEFINITIONS (baked params) instead of being derived from rendered three.js meshes.\n\nENGAGE THE USER FIRST: this phase has real design forks (especially the collider decoupling and the shared/client authority split). Before implementing, raise the OPEN QUESTIONS below with the user and agree on the approach. Do NOT guess or hack past them — surface a short proposal and wait for the call.\n\nOPEN QUESTIONS FOR THE USER: exact module layout inside packages/shared (sim/ protocol/ types/ math/); how AI and weapons split across shared (authoritative logic) vs client (effects only); how much of current shipDynamics / shipPhysics / steering is already pure enough to lift directly.\n\nDONE WHEN: the same input log produces matching state in a Bun (node-env) test and in the browser, both importing packages/shared; collider definitions resolve server-side with no three.js dependency.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Extracted the authoritative sim into a three.js-free packages/shared: POJO vec3/quat math, ship dynamics/thrust/steering, AI pilot (steering PIDs, corridor avoidance, pursuit, combat state), server-authoritative weapons (fire timing, traveling projectiles, swept-raycast hit detection, damage/health), baked GLB colliders, and Rapier running headless under Bun. Proven deterministic + cross-environment (node + happy-dom) via determinism tests. Landed as 3 merged PRs: slice 1 #26 (ship sim core), 2a #27 (AI), 2b #28 (weapons). Deferred (tracked): rewiring the live client to consume shared; dynamic-asteroid authoritative world (noted on Phase 2 k3zbaseh).","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-26T08:41:06.306Z","updated_at":"2026-06-27T19:07:33.689Z","started_at":"2026-06-27T04:01:52.583Z","completed_at":"2026-06-27T19:07:33.689Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
