{"id":"a69foj7x","parent_id":"ia40wzb6","name":"Quick prompt: add subtask (task-detail panel)","description":"Add a new \"Add subtask\" quick prompt to the task-detail panel so the agent can paste it as a `dex create … --parent <id>` instruction.\n\nNothing below is locked — work with the human to confirm slot order, prompt text, max-depth strategy, and naming before/while implementing.\n\n## Scope\n\n- New prompt id (e.g. `add-subtask`) in `src/lib/agentPrompts.ts`, alongside `view` / `start` / `complete` / `delete`.\n- Slot order on the task-detail panel: `view, add-subtask, start, complete, delete`. That puts add-subtask on ⌘2 and shifts start / complete / delete to ⌘3 / ⌘4 / ⌘5.\n- Extend `QUICK_PROMPT_KEY_BINDINGS` in `src/lib/keyboard/quickPromptShortcuts.ts` with `$mod+5 → slotIndex 4`.\n- Workspace-home panel already has a root-level `create` prompt; do not duplicate it there.\n\n## Prompt text\n\nModel on `buildWorkspaceCreatePrompt` (root-task create) but parented:\n\n  dex --config '…' --storage-path '…' create 'TASK_TITLE' --description 'TASK_DESCRIPTION' --parent <selected-task-id>\n\nAgree title/description with the user first; run `show <new-id> --full` after to confirm; do not start the new subtask unless asked.\n\n## Visibility / max-depth gate\n\nThe deepest level dex allows must NOT show this prompt. The human believes the limit is 3 levels (root + 2) but it is unconfirmed — when starting this task, work with the human to verify by:\n  - reading the dex CLI help / man pages\n  - skimming dex source if available\n  - manually creating nested tasks until `create --parent` rejects, then deleting the probe tasks\n\nEncode the confirmed limit as a named constant (e.g. `MAX_TASK_DEPTH`) and extend `visibilityByPromptId` so `add-subtask` returns false when the task is already at the max depth. Depth is walkable from `parentId` chains via the existing task store.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- ⌘1–⌘5 select the five prompts on task-detail in the new order; ⌘C copy still works.\n- `Add subtask` is hidden (or disabled, matching how `start` / `complete` already behave when unavailable) at the deepest level.\n- Tests in `src/lib/agentPrompts.test.ts` and `src/lib/keyboard/quickPromptShortcuts.test.ts` updated for the new slot count and visibility rule.\n- `bun run check`, `bun run typecheck`, `bun run fallow:audit` pass.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Added Add subtask quick prompt (⌘2) on task-detail with dex create --parent instruction; extended ⌘1–⌘5 bindings; gated at MAX_TASK_DEPTH (3) via computeTaskDepth; exported AgentPromptId; tests and fallow/check/typecheck pass.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-07T17:59:09.553Z","updated_at":"2026-06-08T01:44:35.022Z","started_at":"2026-06-08T01:44:35.020Z","completed_at":"2026-06-08T01:44:35.022Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
