{"id":"bcohudeg","parent_id":"0m493lgo","name":"First AI-piloted ship: shared control surface, pursue/get-behind, asteroid avoidance","description":"Add the first non-player ship, flown by AI through the SAME control surface as the player (applyControls(localSteering, throttle, dt)) — never doing anything the player physically could not. Mirrors the Librelancer model: one ShipSteeringComponent-style seam, source switchable between human and autopilot.\n\nIntroduce a Pilot abstraction that each frame yields (localSteering, throttle); the human fly-by-wire becomes one implementation, AI another. Extract the shared pitch/yaw/level-roll PID core out of flyByWire.ts so both paths reuse it (pure + unit-tested, per AGENTS.md).\n\nBehavior ladder (each an independently demoable, pure world->steering step):\n1. Spawn an inert second ship; refactor scriptlancer.ts off its hardcoded single shipBody/shipPhysics.\n2. seek — aim at a target point via the shared PID; fly straight at the player.\n3. getBehind — offset pursuit toward a point behind the players -forward axis (tail-chase).\n4. Asteroid avoidance — port Librelancers probe-and-score idea, but as a heading nudge (blended target point), not strafe, since our ship is forward-thrust only. Add hysteresis to prevent twitch.\n\nNo weapons/shooting in this milestone.\n\nTuning: AI flight params (steering torque, max speed, pursuit offset, avoidance gains) are codified, configurable knobs, defaulting to a slightly handicapped profile so beginners can shake the AI off their tail. AI gets its own tuning constants rather than sharing the players.\n\nNaming note: describe this as our own pilot/behavior model in code and comments — no external game references (per project convention).","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"First AI ship on shared applyControls seam: Pilot abstraction, shared steeringControl PIDs, tail-chase + heading-nudge asteroid avoidance, separate AI_SHIP_TUNING. Player + AI fighters in scriptlancer; AI spawns ahead for easy demo. Review fixes (per-pilot buffers, spawn teardown, cached obstacles). Rebased on main (snappier-rapier); vp check + 117 tests pass.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-24T07:01:45.690Z","updated_at":"2026-06-25T06:07:31.205Z","started_at":"2026-06-25T05:29:04.376Z","completed_at":"2026-06-25T06:07:31.205Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":["rmuexegj","wtysthix","hl9qg145"],"children":[]}
