{"id":"gyft9pnw","parent_id":"ia40wzb6","name":"Middle column (task list) must scroll when content overflows","description":"BUG\nThe middle column in the workspaces layout (the task list at the current zoom level) does not scroll. When there are more tasks than fit vertically, items below the fold are clipped and unreachable. Reproduced visually with the gdex workspace.\n\nCAUSE\n- src/components/TaskBoard/TaskBoard.tsx renders <div class={styles.board}> with `flex: '0 1 13rem'`, `minHeight: 0`, `overflow: 'hidden'` (src/components/TaskList/taskList.css.ts:9-19).\n- The child <ul class={styles.list}> (taskList.css.ts:21-28) has no overflow and no flex sizing, so when content exceeds the board height it is clipped instead of scrolling.\n\nFIX\nApply the same pattern that already works for the sidebar in src/components/WorkspaceSidebar/workspaceSidebar.css.ts:35-43 (`sidebarBody`):\n  - flex: 1\n  - minHeight: 0\n  - overflowX: hidden\n  - overflowY: auto\n\nTwo reasonable shapes — pick whichever keeps the CSS simplest:\n1. Add `flex: 1`, `minHeight: 0`, `overflowY: 'auto'`, `overflowX: 'hidden'` directly to `styles.list` in taskList.css.ts. Smallest change.\n2. Introduce a scroll wrapper div inside `TaskBoard` (between `styles.board` and `<TaskList>`) carrying those properties, so `styles.list` stays purely about layout. Cleaner separation if TaskList ever renders non-<ul> content.\n\nDefault to option 1 unless something pushes us to option 2.\n\nCONSIDER\n- Match the collapsed-sidebar scrollbar-hidden pattern (`scrollbarHidden` in workspaceSidebar.css.ts:68-76) only if a native scrollbar looks bad inside the narrow column; otherwise let it show.\n- Verify behavior at both `flex: '0 1 13rem'` minimum and when the detail panel is open / closed — no horizontal scrollbar, no layout reflow on the right column.\n- Empty / single-task states should not introduce a stray scrollbar.\n\nACCEPTANCE\n- With many tasks in the middle column, the list scrolls vertically inside the board; the breadcrumb and surrounding chrome do not.\n- Light + dark mode both look intentional.\n- No new lint / typecheck / fallow findings.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Fixed: middle TaskList column now scrolls when tasks overflow; applied the WorkspaceSidebar sidebarBody pattern (flex: 1, minHeight: 0, overflowY: auto). Verified check/typecheck/fallow pass.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-01T02:24:33.687Z","updated_at":"2026-06-01T03:11:57.881Z","started_at":"2026-06-01T03:11:57.880Z","completed_at":"2026-06-01T03:11:57.881Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
