{"id":"irrxwdh3","parent_id":"2evkv6xf","name":"Phase 7 — Deploy: Fly.io room servers + Cloudflare matchmaker","description":"CONTEXT: Cheap-at-idle, horizontally scalable hosting for a WebTransport (HTTP/3 over QUIC) server.\n\nINVESTIGATE: Dockerizing the Bun + webtransport-bun server for Fly.io — HTTP/3 needs OPEN UDP PORTS (not just TCP), valid TLS certs in staging/prod (self-signed + cert-hash is local-only), and the N-API/Rust addon must build/bundle in the Docker image (confirm musl/glibc + arch compatibility on Fly). One machine first; scale-to-zero; later the Machines API to spawn a room server on demand. A Cloudflare Worker + Hono stateless lobby/matchmaker hands clients a room + machine address; direct client->machine WebTransport routing (confirm Fly UDP/QUIC routing to a specific machine). Measure per-room CPU/RAM to size the fleet.\n\nOPEN QUESTIONS FOR THE USER: matchmaking/room-assignment policy; region strategy; auth; cert issuance approach on Fly (Fly-managed vs custom).\n\nDONE WHEN: two real clients play over the internet via the matchmaker over WebTransport, and per-room resource cost is documented.\n\nNOTE (deferred from Phase 3): server disconnect robustness. Add an idle timeout / heartbeat so a player who stops sending input is despawned promptly, instead of relying solely on the QUIC session.closed promise — which lags on a browser refresh (no clean close frame), leaving a ghost ship still being simulated for a few seconds.","priority":1,"completed":false,"result":null,"metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-26T08:41:07.103Z","updated_at":"2026-06-28T06:37:23.901Z","started_at":null,"completed_at":null,"blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
