{"id":"jvprxjqg","parent_id":"mzb84gnf","name":"Recipe import: confirm before persist","description":"Curated recipe ingestion: the DB is for **good** data only, not every parse attempt.\n\n## Principle\n- **Scan = preview** (Claude reads the page). **Confirm = commit** (writes + enrichment). Until confirm: no Turso food rows, no Spoonacular, no ingredient resolution that mutates state.\n- **Human gate:** Greg reviews parsed recipe + ingredients and can say “whoa” — discard, or take the URL to an agent session to add golden fixtures / fix prompts before trying again. Bad parses should become **tests**, not permanent rows.\n- **Cost discipline:** Don’t spend Claude or Spoonacular calls on enrichment until the human is happy with the extracted recipe and ingredient list.\n\n## Context (today)\n- Extraction calls `resolveIngredientsAgainstDb` during scan (inserts + optional Spoonacular). Recipe row waits for **Create recipe**.\n- Food tables were wiped 2026-05-18; fresh start for this workflow.\n\n## Child tasks\nImplement confirm-before-persist first (`z3ksyi5w`), then preview/audit UI (`dh34x9uy`), then library UX (source links, markdown, ingredient↔recipes). When extraction quality is wrong, **pause implementation** and work with Greg on goldens — don’t paper over with more auto-insert logic.\n\n## Done when\n- Nothing hits DB or Spoonacular until explicit confirm.\n- Preview UI makes it easy to judge ingredient lines before commit.\n- Subtasks below complete or explicitly deferred with Greg.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Import preview: confirm before persist, ingredient lines, source links, markdown audit UI—all shipped and verified in app.","metadata":{"commit":{"sha":"cc874e7","message":"improve turkey recipe handling","branch":"import-confirm-ui-polish","timestamp":"2026-05-18T07:08:14.155Z"}},"created_at":"2026-05-18T04:12:00.801Z","updated_at":"2026-05-18T07:08:14.157Z","started_at":"2026-05-18T07:08:14.156Z","completed_at":"2026-05-18T07:08:14.157