{"id":"k3zbaseh","parent_id":"2evkv6xf","name":"Phase 2 — Bun WebTransport server: authoritative world, no prediction","description":"CONTEXT: The \"dumb but correct\" first networked milestone. Transport is WebTransport from day one (see parent TRANSPORT decision) — no WebSocket scaffold.\n\nINVESTIGATE: the webtransport-bun package (N-API addon, Rust wtransport crate) to accept HTTP/3 WebTransport connections in Bun and read/write datagrams in the game loop; a thin Transport interface (sendUnreliable/sendReliable/onMessage) so the concrete transport is swappable; running shared/sim headless at 60Hz server-side; the first cut of the shared/ binary protocol (input up as unreliable datagrams, full-state snapshot down at 20Hz as datagrams; reliable stream for join/leave/identity); client rendering server state directly with NO prediction (expect visible lag — that is fine here).\n\nLOCAL-DEV GOTCHA: QUIC/HTTP-3 requires TLS even on localhost. Use a self-signed cert + WebTransport serverCertificateHashes on the client (trust a known cert hash, no CA) so local dev needs no real certs.\n\nOPEN QUESTIONS FOR THE USER: connection/session/room identity model; where the protocol + Transport modules live; whether to bother with any non-WebTransport fallback yet (default: no, require a modern browser for now).\n\nDONE WHEN: two browser tabs connect over WebTransport and see each other flying in one authoritative world.\n\nNOTE (surfaced in Phase 1 slice 2a review): the shared sim currently models asteroids as static `kinematicPositionBased` obstacles in `dogfightWorld` — a deterministic AI/weapons TEST harness, not the real world. The client's asteroids are dynamic: random spin (`asteroidPhysics.ts` MIN/MAX_ASTEROID_SPIN) + mass, so they tumble and get pushed by collisions. The authoritative server world must model the real dynamic asteroid field (seeded initial spin, deterministic via the rapier3d-deterministic-compat build) instead of the static stub, so server state matches client gameplay. Fold this into the client-rewire so client and server share one world model.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Bun WebTransport (HTTP/3/QUIC) server live (PR #31, merged to main): authoritative 60Hz sim / ~20Hz snapshots, hand-rolled binary protocol over a swappable Transport (+ in-process loopback), idempotent local-dev TLS cert with server-emits/root-distributes hash via 'bun run dev'. Networked client (?server=) renders server entity state, sends input ~30Hz. Naive netcode by design — no prediction/interpolation, lag visible (Phases 3/4 address it). Includes dev-ergonomics cleanups, vitest .claude exclude, and the inverted-yaw fix.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-26T08:41:06.440Z","updated_at":"2026-06-28T06:07:31.543Z","started_at":"2026-06-27T19:09:27.217Z","completed_at":"2026-06-28T06:07:31.543Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
{"id":"k4iqhjrm","parent_id":"zgbnfktr","name":"Tool: Silhouette Studio — interactive 3D model → SVG icon (/tools)","description":"New self-contained tool page at /tools/silhouette-studio/: drop a GLB, pose it live (mouse + three synced sliders), preview, and export a clean single-path SVG icon. Contained entirely to this tool — no logic imported by shared components. No blog entry. Homepage link via projects.ts added last, only when ready.\n\nReuse: Port the pure silhouette pipeline from scriptlancer branch feat/model-to-svg-roll-buttons (tools/model-to-svg/modelToSvg.ts — buildCulledScene + emitFlatSvg, clipper-lib union/offset + hand-rolled Douglas-Peucker; flat-only). For the loader, use three GLTFLoader (three is needed for the live viewport anyway), NOT gltf-transform — feed parseAsync an ArrayBuffer from the dropped File. The resolveOptions/buildCulledScene/emitFlatSvg split already isolates load->cull->emit; for live preview, hoist loadMesh out so the mesh is cached once and only pose->project->union->emit re-runs (debounced).\n\nInteraction: Three sliders = bank/pitch/spin (spin is a free 2D in-plane rotation); bidirectional sync with a trackball drag; fixed orthographic scan camera matching the pipeline CAMPOS; snap-to-15deg + reset; locked pose (bank 40 / pitch 6 / spin -18) as a preset. Axis-remap (forward/up) for arbitrary models.\n\nDual preview: scan-frame overlay on the 3D canvas + live SVG pane rendering the actual exported path.\n\nStyleable output: emit a single path with fill=currentColor, fixed 0 0 512 512 viewBox, no width/height — deterministic bytes per (model, pose, options). Default currentColor; optional var(--icon-color, currentColor) toggle and aria-hidden / title toggle. Demonstrate recoloring with a native input type=color bound to the inline preview color (plus optional opacity slider for alpha); no color-picker dependency. Surface copy-paste usage snippets (inline + mask-image for external-file use) so consumers avoid the img/currentColor gotcha.\n\nAstro integration: routes src/pages/tools/index.astro + tools/silhouette-studio.astro (breadcrumbs auto-derive). Add a fullBleed prop to BaseLayout so this page escapes the prose column. bun add three clipper-lib — no CDN; import only from the page client script, dynamic-import the heavy libs on first model drop so other pages/chunks stay untouched.\n\nSource reference: /Users/greg.linscheid/greg_projects/scriptlancer @ feat/model-to-svg-roll-buttons.","priority":1,"completed":false,"result":null,"metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-27T19:57:22.130Z","updated_at":"2026-06-27T23:36:07.814Z","started_at":"2026-06-27T23:36:07.813Z","completed_at":null,"blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
