{"id":"lbyqyqsy","parent_id":"zgbnfktr","name":"Migrate content from astro-greg","description":"Port the live site content and structure from the legacy repo into greglinscheid.com (Vite+ / Astro 6). This is a **collaborative** milestone — pause and discuss tradeoffs with Greg before locking in architecture choices.\n\n## Prerequisite\n\nComplete sibling task **tzffvzms** (Wire CI and quality tooling) first, or at minimum have Vite+ / Astro dev/build working in the target repo.\n\n## Source repo\n\n- **Local:** `/Users/greg.linscheid/greg_projects/astro-greg`\n- **GitHub:** https://github.com/Vilos92/astro-greg\n- **Stack (legacy):** Astro 5, Tailwind 3 + `@tailwindcss/typography`, React islands (breadcrumbs only), MDX pages, content collections, Prettier/ESLint/husky\n\n## Target repo\n\n- **Local:** `/Users/greg.linscheid/greg_projects/greglinscheid.com`\n- **Stack (new):** Astro 6 + Vite+ (Oxfmt/Oxlint). Styling TBD — **Vanilla Extract is preferred** (family pattern from gdex/vilos92) but discuss Astro integration with Greg if awkward.\n\n## Human-in-the-loop (required)\n\nBefore implementing each major area, **ask Greg** when multiple valid approaches exist. Do not 1:1 port legacy decisions without discussion. Explicitly open topics:\n\n1. **Styling** — legacy uses Tailwind + typography plugin + Bear Blog–derived `global.css` (green theme, Atkinson font). New site need **not** reuse Tailwind. Vanilla Extract is the default direction; confirm tokens, layout width (~720px main), dark mode strategy.\n2. **Code blocks / syntax highlighting** — legacy relies on Astro/Shiki defaults + Tailwind `prose` overrides (`Prose.astro`). It's 2026; propose modern approach (Astro built-in, or simpler CSS) and get sign-off — **do not copy the old Prose/Tailwind setup blindly**.\n3. **Routing & pages** — legacy routes: `/` (home MDX), `/blog`, `/blog/[slug]`, `/404`, `/500`, `/rss.xml`. Routing can be redesigned if cleaner; **discuss** before changing URLs (SEO/bookmarks).\n4. **Breadcrumbs** — legacy uses a React island (`Breadcrumbs.tsx` wrapped by `Breadcrumbs.astro`). Worked fine but was a quick build; open to pure Astro, simpler nav, or dropping breadcrumbs — **ask Greg**.\n5. **What to drop vs re-implement** — some legacy sections may be trimmed or rewritten; confirm with Greg rather than assuming parity.\n\n## Content inventory (migrate / preserve)\n\n### Blog articles (keep both; light cleanup OK)\n\n| Slug | File | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `hello-world` | `src/content/blog/hello-world.md` | **Must amend:** note it was written for the old site; link to https://github.com/Vilos92/astro-greg |\n| `copyparty-tunnel` | `src/content/blog/copyparty-tunnel.md` | Long technical guide; keep substance, tidy prose/formatting if needed |\n\nContent schema (legacy `src/content/config.ts`): `title`, `description`, `pubDate`, optional `updatedDate`, optional `heroImage`.\n\n### Home page (`src/pages/index.mdx`)\n\nRich MDX home: portrait, blog teaser (latest post link), software projects lists (MilkTea, copyparty-tunnel, milo-engine, typerion, etc.), other links (dotfiles, FreshRSS), contact/resume, acknowledgements, dedication images. **Review with Greg** — update \"You're looking at it now\" / github links to point at new repo; drop or refresh stale project entries as needed.\n\n### Static assets (`public/`)\n\n- `greg-portrait.jpg`, `milo-index.jpg`, `milo.png`\n- `Resume - Greg Linscheid.pdf`\n- `favicon.ico`\n- `fonts/atkinson-{regular,bold}.woff`\n- `blog/hello-world.jpg`, `blog/copyparty.svg`, `blog/copyparty-2025-08-15.png`\n\n### Site metadata (`src/consts.ts`)\n\n- `SITE_TITLE`: Greg Linscheid\n- `SITE_DESCRIPTION`: A personal website for Greg Linscheid\n- `formatTitle()` helper\n\n### Features to port (implementation flexible)\n\n- Astro **content collection** for blog + Zod schema\n- Blog index + `[...slug]` post pages + `BlogPost` layout\n- **RSS** feed (`src/pages/rss.xml.js` → adapt for Astro 6 / `@astrojs/rss`)\n- **Sitemap** (legacy `@astrojs/sitemap`; add if deploy target needs it)\n- `BaseHead` (meta, OG/Twitter, canonical, font preload)\n- `FormattedDate`, `Footer`\n- Error pages `404.mdx`, `500.mdx`\n\n### Legacy integrations — do NOT port as-is\n\n- Tailwind / `@astrojs/tailwind` / typography plugin\n- React (`@astrojs/react`) unless Greg agrees breadcrumbs need it\n- Prettier / ESLint / husky / lint-staged (replaced by Vite+ in target repo)\n- `site: 'https://example.com'` placeholder — set real production URL with Greg\n\n## Suggested approach\n\n1. Read astro-greg source; list pages, components, and assets.\n2. **Checkpoint with Greg:** styling direction (VE?), routing, breadcrumbs, syntax highlighting.\n3. Set up Astro integrations in target (`@astrojs/mdx`, content collections, rss, sitemap as needed).\n4. Copy/migrate content files and `public/` assets.\n5. Rebuild layouts/components in chosen style system.\n6. Amend **Hello World** post per requirement above.\n7. Update home page links (new repo, retired projects).\n8. Run target validation loop: `vp check`, `bun run typecheck`, `bun run test`, `bun run fallow:audit`.\n9. `bun run build` + spot-check routes locally.\n\n## Out of scope (unless Greg asks)\n\n- Deploy / DNS / hosting cutover\n- New blog posts beyond migrating existing two\n- Portfolio section beyond what's on the current home page\n\n## Verify before completing\n\n- `/`, `/blog`, `/blog/hello-world`, `/blog/copyparty-tunnel`, `/rss.xml`, `/404` render correctly\n- Hello World links to Vilos92/astro-greg and states legacy context\n- Assets (images, PDF, fonts) load\n- `vp check` and CI-equivalent commands pass\n- Greg has signed off on any intentional URL or content drops\n\nDo **not** commit unless Greg asks. Do **not** start this dex task unless asked.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Migrated astro-greg content into greglinscheid.com (PR #1): blog posts, home page, assets, VE styling, pure-Astro breadcrumbs, RSS/sitemap, 404/500. Hello-world legacy note; vp check/test/fallow/build pass.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-07T16:10:54.258Z","updated_at":"2026-06-07T17:21:56.473Z","started_at":"2026-06-07T16:17:57.180Z","completed_at":"2026-06-07T17:21:56.473Z","blockedBy":["tzffvzms"],"blocks":["3cc9jmf0"],"children":[]}
