{"id":"lsidb0yp","parent_id":"0m493lgo","name":"Ship destruction explosion VFX","description":"Procedural explosion effect triggered when a ship's onDeath callback fires (createShipHealth in src/game/ship/shipHealth.ts). Modeled after LibreLancer's approach: a single co-located visual + audio event at the ship's world position, no multi-stage cutscene.\n\nVisual stages (all procedural — no external assets required):\n1. Central additive flash: scaled-up version of the existing ImpactBurst (src/game/weapon/impactBurst.ts) — brighter, slower fade (~0.8 s).\n2. Expanding shockwave ring: a thin torus or billboard ring sprite that scales outward and fades over ~0.5 s.\n3. Debris sprites: 6–10 small point sprites that shoot outward from origin with a slight downward drift, fading over ~1–1.5 s.\n4. Lingering fire/smoke sprite: a soft radial sprite (orange/grey tint) that fades over ~1.5–2 s.\n\nImplementation pattern:\n- New file src/game/weapon/createExplosion.ts (or src/game/vfx/createExplosion.ts).\n- Factory returns a SceneResource + tick(dt): boolean lifecycle, exactly like ImpactBurst. Returns false when all stages are finished so the caller can despawn.\n- Reuse DataTexture + Sprite + AdditiveBlending from impactBurst.ts. The shockwave ring can be a scaled Sprite with a ring-shaped DataTexture (donut alpha mask).\n- Spawned via entityRegistry (same pattern as ImpactEffects.spawn in src/game/weapon/impactEffects.ts).\n- Sound hook: call a provided onBoom?: (position: Vector3) => void callback at spawn time so scriptlancer.ts can wire in audio (asset TBD — user will supply a boom sound file).\n\nHookup in scriptlancer.ts:\n- The existing playerHealth and enemyHealth are created with createShipHealth(onDeath). Extend the onDeath callbacks to also spawn an explosion at the ship's current world position before respawning.\n- Hide the exploding ship immediately (object.visible = false) so it doesn't overlap the VFX; restore on respawn.\n\nValidation: vp check && vp test after implementation.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Procedural ship-destruction VFX: multi-stage explosion (flash, shockwave ring, debris, smoke) via createExplosion + explosionEffects entity pool; hooked to player/enemy onDeath with ship hidden + boom audio callback. Later pass: 128px textures, linear filtering, softer falloff. Tests in createExplosion.test.ts and explosionEffects.test.ts. vp check && vp test pass.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-26T04:07:27.223Z","updated_at":"2026-06-26T05:26:25.031Z","started_at":"2026-06-26T04:08:31.469Z","completed_at":"2026-06-26T05:26:25.031Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
