{"id":"oobeapzz","parent_id":"ia40wzb6","name":"Agent instruction snippets: design + implementation","description":"The cornerstone feature of gdex: surfacing quick copy/paste instructions for agents, tied to dex operations.\n\n## Locked design (2026-05-23)\n\n**Section title:** Quick prompts\n\n**Location:** Bottom of the right-hand detail panel (below description, result, blockers, subtasks).\n\n**Interaction:** Flat `<select>` — copy-on-select with brief \"Copied!\" feedback (same pattern as task ID copy). Interpolate `{task_id}` and active workspace name into `gdex <workspace> …` commands.\n\n**v1 snippets (order):**\n1. **Start task** — kick off / mark in progress (first item; highest priority)\n2. **Mark complete** — `gdex <workspace> complete {task_id} --result \"…\"`\n3. **Delete task** — safe delete with subtask cascade warning\n\n**Deferred:** Update description snippet (cut from v1).\n\n**Follow-up:** Subtask `farzygud` — right-click task list context menu (\"Copy start task quick prompt\", extensible).\n\n**Still default unless changed:** flat select (not grouped); copy-on-select only (no preview); conditional visibility TBD (e.g. hide start when already in progress, hide complete when done).","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Quick prompts in detail panel (select + code block + copy), agentPrompts.ts snippets, component reorg and AGENTS conventions.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-05-22T06:10:28.815Z","updated_at":"2026-05-23T16:05:12.692Z","started_at":"2026-05-23T05:42:26.053Z","completed_at":"2026-05-23T16:05:12.692Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":["farzygud"]}
{"id":"opo6ygoq","parent_id":"0m493lgo","name":"Weapon impact VFX: flash + light on bolt hit (Librelancer-style)","description":"Add a Freelancer/Librelancer-style projectile IMPACT effect: when a laser bolt hits an\nasteroid it currently just despawns (\"vanishes\") with no acknowledgement. Spawn a short-lived,\nself-expiring visual burst at the contact point instead. This is the impact/flash only — NOT\nasteroid destruction (that is a separate, later concern).\n\nNorth star (Librelancer ProjectileManager.Update): on raycast contact it kills the bolt and calls\nSpawnTempFx(HitEffect, contactPoint) — a fire-and-forget particle effect placed at the contact\npoint (translation only, no orientation) that plays out and removes itself. The hit FX fires ONLY\non contact, never on lifetime/TTL expiry. We mirror that structure in three.js.\n\nLandable scope (decided): FLASH + BRIEF LIGHT only. Spark particles are an explicit follow-up\nstep below, not part of this slice.\n\nCurrent code (read these first):\n- src/game/weapon/projectile.ts — a bolt is a `SceneResource & { tick(dt): boolean }` (additive\n  CylinderGeometry, color 0x44aaff, MUZZLE_VELOCITY, LIFETIME). Match this shape/tone.\n- src/game/weapon/weaponSystem.ts — `checkCollision(slot)` sphere-tests bolts vs asteroids;\n  `advanceSlot` returns \"kill this bolt\" on EITHER collision OR lifetime expiry; `despawnSlots`\n  calls `entityRegistry.despawn(id)`. THAT despawn is the exact \"vanishes\" moment and the hook point.\n- src/game/entityRegistry.ts — spawn/despawn/despawnAll; mint ids with createEntityId().\n- src/game/sceneResource.ts — SceneResource contract { object, destroy }.\n- src/game/createThrusterEffects.ts — reference tone for additive VFX (AdditiveBlending,\n  depthWrite:false, dispose every geometry/material).\n- src/game/scriptlancer.ts — single setAnimationLoop with clamped dt; weaponSystem created ~line 98,\n  updated ~line 150; teardown in destroy() (~172) and the catch path (~182).\n\nImplementation:\n1. src/game/weapon/impactBurst.ts — `createImpactBurst(position)` returns\n   `SceneResource & { tick(dt): boolean }` (same shape as Projectile). Contents:\n   - A camera-facing additive FLASH (three.js Sprite + SpriteMaterial, AdditiveBlending,\n     depthWrite:false, transparent), color matching the bolt (~0x44aaff). Animate scale 0 -> peak ->\n     0 and opacity fade over ~0.15-0.25s. tick returns false when the burst is finished.\n   - A brief PointLight whose intensity decays to 0 over the same window. Per AGENTS three.js rules,\n     a PointLight (no shadow map) needs NO GPU dispose — it is removed when its parent group is\n     removed; do NOT wrap a no-op destroy around it. The Sprite's texture+material DO need dispose().\n   - Position-only placement (mesh/group.position.copy(position)); no orientation to the surface\n     normal (matches Librelancer translation-only). Build a tiny generated radial-gradient texture for\n     the flash (CanvasTexture) and dispose it in destroy(), OR a known asset — keep it framework-light.\n2. src/game/weapon/impactEffects.ts — the SpawnTempFx/tempFx analog:\n   `createImpactEffects(entityRegistry)` -> `{ spawn(position), update(dt), destroy() }`. Holds a live\n   list of { id, burst }; spawn() mints an id, creates a burst, entityRegistry.spawn(id, burst), pushes\n   to the list; update(dt) ticks each burst and entityRegistry.despawn(id)s + removes the ones whose\n   tick returned false (mirror weaponSystem.despawnSlots reverse-index splice); destroy() despawns all\n   remaining. @sideEffect tags throughout.\n3. Wire the hook in weaponSystem.ts: add an `onImpact?: (position: Vector3) => void` option (keep VFX\n   out of weapon logic). Split the kill path so a COLLISION kill captures\n   slot.projectile.object.position.clone() and calls onImpact, while LIFETIME EXPIRY stays silent\n   (matches Librelancer: hit FX on contact only). Suggest having advanceSlot/checkCollision report\n   WHY the bolt died rather than a bare boolean.\n4. Wire scriptlancer.ts: const impactEffects = createImpactEffects(entityRegistry); pass\n   { onImpact: p => impactEffects.spawn(p) } into createWeaponSystem; call impactEffects.update(dt) in\n   the loop right after weaponSystem.update; impactEffects.destroy() in BOTH the destroy() and catch\n   teardown paths (same pattern as weaponSystem).\n\nTests (vitest, environment node — three.js objects construct fine, see entityRegistry.test.ts /\ncreateDustField.test.ts):\n- impactEffects.test.ts: spawn a burst, tick past its duration, assert it was despawned from the\n  registry and the live list is empty; destroy() clears all.\n- impactBurst.test.ts: tick lifetime returns false after the duration; (optionally) opacity/scale\n  follow the expected envelope.\n\nFollow-up step (NOT this slice): add a spark spray — a small additive three.js Points burst (~6-10\npoints) ejected along radial directions with per-particle velocity, fading out, ticked + disposed by\nthe same impactBurst. Track as its own step once flash+light lands.\n\nConventions (AGENTS.md): #/ imports with .ts suffix; `type` over `interface`; `undefined` over `null`;\n@sideEffect tags naming the effect; dispose ALL GPU resources (geometry, material, textures) and pair\nevery allocation with teardown; keep three.js out of the Preact UI layer; section comments\n(/* Types. */ /* Constants. */ /* Helpers. */). Comments explain WHY, not what; no references to other\ngames (Freelancer/Librelancer) in code comments — describe this project's own design.\nValidate: vp check -> vp test -> bun run fallow:audit (wire any new exports or the audit flags them).","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Added impact burst VFX (additive sprite flash + decaying point light) on bolt-asteroid collision via impactBurst.ts and impactEffects.ts; wired onImpact hook in weaponSystem and scriptlancer. Collision-only (no FX on lifetime expiry). Tests + vp check/test/fallow:audit pass.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-24T04:52:47.480Z","updated_at":"2026-06-24T05:20:10.702Z","started_at":"2026-06-24T04:53:35.843Z","completed_at":"2026-06-24T05:20:10.702Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
