{"id":"q6t535u3","parent_id":"0m493lgo","name":"Add master bus limiter + gain-staging","description":"Output amplitude is emergent — 8-voice fire pool, impacts, collisions, and engine loop can stack and clip (harsh crackle). Standard game-audio practice (FMOD/Wwise ship master limiters). Gain-stage per-source volumes so the normal sum has headroom, then insert a DynamicsCompressorNode on the listener output (listener.gain -> compressor -> destination) as a clip safety net, disposed on teardown. Note: it is a safety net, not a mix substitute — tune threshold so it only catches peaks, not constant pumping. ~10 lines, contained to createGameAudio.ts. Related: builds on the engine audio fix in task 20au5fho.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Gain-staged engine (0.45), weapon fire (0.18), and positional one-shots (0.55); inserted DynamicsCompressorNode on listener output via setFilter (threshold -3 dB, ratio 20:1), removed on teardown. vp check and vp test pass.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-25T01:48:58.209Z","updated_at":"2026-06-25T05:22:27.486Z","started_at":"2026-06-25T04:55:58.190Z","completed_at":"2026-06-25T05:22:27.486Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
{"id":"qnbk384g","parent_id":"0m493lgo","name":"Positional audio: throttle-scaled engine + weapon fire/impact + ship collision (three.js Web Audio)","description":"Add positional audio to the game using three.js (r0.184) built-in Web Audio\nsupport: AudioListener + PositionalAudio + Audio + AudioLoader. This is the\nmodern 2026 three.js audio path — there is no newer official API.\n\n== Goal: four sounds ==\n1. ENGINE LOOP that scales with throttle (layered idle+thrust crossfade).\n2. WEAPON FIRE one-shot when a projectile is fired.\n3. PROJECTILE IMPACT one-shot when a bolt hits an asteroid.\n4. SHIP COLLISION one-shot when the ship hits an asteroid.\n\nScope: ONE subtask covering the audio FOUNDATION plus all four integrations.\n\n== Audio files (provided by the human) ==\nPlace under src/game/assets/audio/ (new dir; mirrors assets/models, assets/shaders).\nWeb-friendly format (.ogg preferred, .mp3 fallback). Expect roughly:\n  - engine idle loop, engine thrust loop (layered crossfade — see #1)\n  - weapon fire one-shot\n  - projectile impact one-shot\n  - ship collision one-shot\nDO NOT invent placeholder audio. If files are missing, fail loud/early per\nAGENTS.md \"Fail fast\" (throw on a required-but-missing asset). Confirm exact\nfilenames/format with the human before wiring.\n\n== 3D strategy (DECIDED) ==\nStereo own-ship, 3D for world. Rationale specific to THIS project's chase\ncamera (src/game/camera/chaseCamera.ts) which LEADS/LAGS the ship during turns:\n  - OWN-SHIP sounds (engine layers + own guns): plain THREE.Audio (non-\n    positional). Centered/present, and immune to \"swim\"/Doppler artifacts that\n    a positional own-ship source would get as the chase cam swings on every\n    bank/turn.\n  - WORLD events (projectile->asteroid impact, ship->asteroid collision, and\n    future other-ship guns): THREE.PositionalAudio attached at the event\n    location, panned/attenuated against the AudioListener, velocity set for\n    subtle Doppler.\nAttach a single AudioListener to the PerspectiveCamera so panning matches the\nview.\n\n== AudioContext unlock (REQUIRED) ==\nBrowsers suspend the Web Audio AudioContext until a user gesture. Resume it on\nthe first user interaction (pointerdown/keydown) — likely inside or alongside\nattachFlyByWire's input setup (src/game/controls/flyByWire.ts attaches canvas\nlisteners already). Until unlocked, sounds must no-op gracefully, not throw.\n\n== Integration points (all already exist in code) ==\n- Render loop: src/game/scriptlancer.ts single renderer.setAnimationLoop. Throttle\n  is already read each frame as flightControls.getThrottle() (scriptlancer.ts\n  ~L161, feeding thrusterEffects.update) — mirror that to drive the engine loop's\n  per-frame pitch/volume.\n- Engine (#1): map throttle (0..1) to BOTH playbackRate (pitch) and volume on\n  the idle/thrust THREE.Audio loops, crossfading idle<->thrust across the\n  throttle range. (Reference: Freelancer's CEngineComponent does\n  pitch = 1 + lerp(min,max,speed)/100, volume = lerp(min,max,speed), and cross-\n  activates rumble/character/cruise layers by speed threshold. Don't copy\n  numbers — tune by ear.)\n- Weapon fire (#2): src/game/weapon/weaponSystem.ts fireWeapons() currently has\n  NO fire callback. Add an onFire(position) option mirroring the existing\n  onImpact option (WeaponSystemOptions). Play own-gun fire as stereo THREE.Audio\n  (own-ship). NOTE: support overlapping/rapid shots — a single Audio node can't\n  retrigger while playing; pool AudioBufferSourceNodes or multiple Audio nodes.\n- Projectile impact (#3): onImpact(position) callback ALREADY wired in\n  scriptlancer.ts (~L102) -> impactEffects.spawn(position). Add a PositionalAudio\n  one-shot at that position alongside the VFX.\n- Ship collision (#4): src/game/physics/createPhysicsWorld.ts exposes\n  onCollisionStart(handler) (L173) but scriptlancer.ts does NOT subscribe yet.\n  Subscribe, identify ship-vs-asteroid pairs (the ship PhysicsEntity is the one\n  registered via registerDynamic for ship.object), and play a PositionalAudio\n  one-shot at the contact. Consider a small debounce so a multi-contact collision\n  doesn't machine-gun the sound.\n\n== three.js lifetime rules (AGENTS.md \"three.js\") ==\n- DISPOSE everything. Audio buffers, AudioContext, and any PositionalAudio nodes\n  must be torn down. Add audio teardown to BOTH the success destroy() and the\n  catch() error path in createScriptlancer (mirrors thrusterEffects/weaponSystem/\n  impactEffects handling).\n- Keep three.js OUT of the Preact UI layer (App.tsx/main.tsx). All audio lives\n  under src/game/. Suggested new module(s): src/game/audio/ (e.g. an audio system\n  factory that owns the listener, loads buffers, and exposes\n  playFire/playImpact/playCollision/updateEngine).\n- Pure vs effectful: keep any mapping math (throttle->pitch/volume curve,\n  crossfade weights) as PURE tested helpers (e.g. src/game/audio/engineAudio.ts\n  with a colocated .test.ts, environment node), with the effectful three.js shell\n  separate and @sideEffect-tagged.\n\n== Conventions (AGENTS.md) ==\n#/ imports with explicit .ts suffix; type over interface; undefined over null;\n@sideEffect tags naming the effect; no forEach (for..of); brace all blocks;\nsection comment blocks. CODE COMMENTS: describe THIS project's design only — do\nNOT name Freelancer/Librelancer/other games in code comments (that context lives\nhere in the task, not the source).\n\n== Librelancer/Freelancer reference (research findings) ==\n- Engine: throttle-scaled looping LAYERS with pitch+gain tracking speed (above).\n- Weapon fire: Munition.one_shot_sound, played positionally at the hardpoint on\n  spawn (PlayProjectileSound). One-shot.\n- Projectile impact: Freelancer has NO dedicated impact-sound field — it only\n  spawns the visual HitEffect; any impact audio is folded into the ALE effect.\n  So our explicit impact sound (#3) is a DELIBERATE divergence/improvement.\n- Ship collision: Freelancer effectively SKIPS non-destructive collision sounds\n  (no scrape/hull-impact sound found in source; audio is reserved for\n  destruction/explosions). Our collision sound (#4) is also a deliberate\n  addition beyond the reference.\n\n== Validation (before commit, AGENTS.md) ==\n1) vp check  2) vp test  3) bun run fallow:audit\nAdd a .fallowrc.jsonc entry if a new audio entrypoint trips unused-export audit;\nask the human before any permanent ignore or baseline refresh.\n\n== Related ==\nSibling subtask jke0r8bn (projectile weapons) is in progress, but the weapon\nsystem, onImpact callback, and physics collision events ALREADY exist in code,\nso audio can proceed against current main without blocking.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Positional audio shipped: three.js AudioListener + stereo engine loop (throttle crossfade), pooled weapon fire, positional impact/collision one-shots; wired into scriptlancer, weaponSystem onFire/onImpact, physics collision handler with debounce. Real Splice assets in src/game/assets/audio/. Review fixes: collision debounce init, positional teardown on destroy, catch-path cleanup order. vp check/test + fallow:audit pass.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-24T05:29:37.013Z","updated_at":"2026-06-24T06:29:34.050Z","started_at":"2026-06-24T05:32:08.498Z","completed_at":"2026-06-24T06:29:34.050Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
