{"id":"sziot1v0","parent_id":"ia40wzb6","name":"Restyle WorkspaceResizer so it doesn't read as a scrollbar","description":"FOLLOW-UP TO hwyhgcu3\n\nPROBLEM\nThe current WorkspaceResizer handle visually reads as a macOS overlay scrollbar:\n- src/components/WorkspaceResizer/workspaceResizer.css.ts\n- width: '0.5rem' (~8px) + borderRadius: '4px' (= half the width → fully rounded pill)\n- alignSelf: 'stretch' (full-height vertical bar) in the gutter\n- subtle palette.border / palette.borderDark fill at rest\n\nThat silhouette is indistinguishable from a scrollbar at rest, so the affordance is unclear until you happen to hover and see col-resize.\n\nGOAL\nKeep the resizer present and discoverable, but visually distinct from a scrollbar. The hit area can stay generous (~0.5rem); the rendered indicator should not.\n\nIDEAS TO EXPLORE (pick one, not all)\n- Thin vertical rule (1–2px) centered in a wider transparent hit area, rather than a rounded pill that fills the gutter.\n- Center grip dots / short hash marks (•••) that only appear on hover/focus.\n- Keep a hairline at rest; thicken + tint on hover/focus/data-dragging.\n- Use a non-pill border-radius (e.g. 1px or 0) so it stops mimicking the scrollbar shape.\n\nCONSTRAINTS (carry-over from hwyhgcu3)\n- Vanilla Extract only; tokens via palette / tokens.ts.\n- Light + dark both look intentional.\n- Quiet at rest, clearly interactive on hover/focus, obvious during drag (data-dragging=\"true\").\n- Don't shrink the actual pointer hit area — only the visual indicator.\n\nACCEPTANCE\n- Side-by-side with the system scrollbar, the divider is not mistakable for one.\n- Hover / focus / drag states still feel native.\n- No new lint/typecheck findings.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Restyled WorkspaceResizer: transparent 0.5rem hit gutter with centered 1px hairline (`::before`), 2px + palette.accent on hover/drag; no longer reads as macOS scrollbar pill. CSS-only in workspaceResizer.css.ts; checks pass.","metadata":null,"c