{"id":"wmozjx6s","parent_id":"0m493lgo","name":"In-game styles: Vanilla Extract for HUD/UI","description":"Adopt @vanilla-extract/css for all in-game DOM styling (Preact shell + HUD overlays).\n\nCurrent state: global src/style.css with BEM-style class names; HUD modules assign className strings and occasionally mutate element.style for dynamic values (touch throttle fill, pressed state, fly-by-wire cursor).\n\nGoal:\n- Add Vanilla Extract + Vite plugin; colocate *.css.ts files with HUD/UI modules (e.g. rollButtons, spectateOverlay, touchThrottleHud, App).\n- Replace global style.css class rules with typed style exports; keep shared tokens (e.g. --hud-aim palette) in a theme/tokens module.\n- Use recipes or style variants for states (pressed, hidden, left/right) instead of stringly className composition where practical.\n- Leave imperative element.style only where values are truly runtime-driven (e.g. throttle fill %, canvas cursor) — document the boundary in AGENTS.md if we codify it.\n\nDone when: no global HUD CSS file remains; vp check passes; HUD looks unchanged in browser (mobile roll buttons, touch throttle, spectate overlay, app fullscreen).","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Migrated all in-game DOM styling to @vanilla-extract/css. Deleted global src/style.css; added colocated .css.ts (App, rollButtons, spectateOverlay, touchThrottleHud) + global.css.ts. Tokens are a typed createGlobalTheme(':root') palette restoring the --hud-aim* CSS custom properties; UI state rides on data-* attributes; touch-throttle fill flows through createVar + setElementVar (@vanilla-extract/dynamic). Imperative element.style kept only for the throttle sync-invisibility opacity init and the fly-by-wire canvas cursor. AGENTS.md gained a Styling section. vp check + vp test (183) + fallow audit all green. Committed 96a3b46 on branch vanilla-extract-hud (pushed); PR + browser smoke-check left to human.","metadata":{"commit":{"sha":"690e045","message":":recycle: Mirror right roll 