{"id":"wtysthix","parent_id":"0m493lgo","name":"AI obstacle avoidance: spatial queries + raycast probes","description":"Upgrade AI heading-nudge avoidance from coarse asteroid bounding spheres to\npath-corridor probing with spatial neighborhood queries and Rapier raycasts —\nstill outputting a blended pursuit target (not strafe), because our ship is\nforward-thrust only.\n\nLibrelancer's AutopilotObstacleAvoidance scores lateral candidates and drives\nstrafe; we keep the probe-and-score idea but adapt the output to a heading nudge\non the aim point (per bcohudeg). Describe the implementation in our own terms\nin code and comments.\n\nContext (after bcohudeg):\n- blendTargetWithAvoidance in src/game/pilot/asteroidAvoidance.ts scores forward-\n  cone probes against ObstacleSample[] from collectAsteroidObstacles.\n- Rapier sim in createPhysicsWorld; asteroid Object3D positions sync each frame\n  after sim.step/sync.\n\nSuggested steps:\n1. Pure probe/score module: path-aligned corridor (ahead length clamped by\n   distance-to-target), multiple lateral candidate headings, threat scoring —\n   colocate unit tests (no Rapier required for core math).\n2. Rapier raycasts or shape casts from the ship along the path direction and\n   candidate offsets; filter self, pursued target, and non-obstacles.\n3. Spatial narrow-phase: query nearby physics entities or a lightweight bucket\n   before ray work — avoid scanning the whole asteroid field every frame.\n4. Preserve hysteresis (separate enter/exit thresholds and a short hold timer\n   before clearing avoidance); wire into createAiPilot without changing player\n   flight.\n5. Optional dev-only debug lines for probe corridors (behind a flag) to tune\n   gains visually.\n\nTuning: codify probe length, corridor half-width, max blend weight, and\nhysteresis delays as named AI-only constants (not shared with player tuning).\n\nConventions: AGENTS.md. Validate vp check → vp test → fallow:audit.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Replaced coarse bounding-sphere avoidance with corridor-probe system: path-aligned rectangular tunnel, 12 lateral candidates scored by obstacle overlap/distance + Rapier raycasts, AABB spatial pre-filter, hold-timer hysteresis. Debug wireframe overlay gated behind ?debug URL param. 24 new unit tests, all 161 tests pass, vp check clean.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-25T05:34:46.022Z","updated_at":"2026-06-25T07:07:03.487Z","started_at":"2026-06-25T06:40:13.278Z","completed_at":"2026-06-25T07:07:03.487Z","blockedBy":["bcohudeg"],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
{"id":"xgfkvvrt","parent_id":"0m493lgo","name":"Death cam: spectate enemy on player death","description":"On player death, suppress flight input and smoothly re-target the chase camera onto the enemy ship, letting the player watch until they choose to respawn. This goes beyond what LibreLancer does (it simply freezes the camera at last position) — this is a deliberate UX enhancement.\n\nState machine to add in scriptlancer.ts:\n  flying → dead (spectating) → respawning → flying\n\nflying → dead:\n- Player onDeath fires.\n- Freeze flight input: flightControls exposes a way to disable input (or check a flag before applying controls in the render loop).\n- Re-target the chase camera: updateChaseCamera (src/game/camera/chaseCamera.ts) takes a plain Object3D — swap the target from playerShip.object to aiShip.object. No changes needed to chaseCamera.ts itself.\n- Hide HUD elements: suppress playerHealthBar, reticle/centerMarker, aimIndicator, leadIndicator during spectate.\n- Show a minimal \"spectating\" UI overlay (plain 2D canvas or DOM element — keep it simple).\n- AI enters loiter mode: when the player is dead the AI has no target. Add a simple loiter behavior to createAiPilot (src/game/pilot/createAiPilot.ts) — fly forward on last heading (zero steering demand, hold throttle) rather than standing still or erroring.\n\ndead → respawning:\n- Triggered by: left mouse click OR a configurable max-spectate timer (e.g. 10 s). Whichever comes first.\n- Brief transition: camera smoothly re-targets back to playerShip.object before restoring input. A 1–2 s re-orient before re-enabling controls feels better than an instant snap.\n\nrespawning → flying:\n- Restore flight controls, re-show HUD, clear spectate overlay.\n- AI re-acquires playerShip as its pursuit target.\n\nKey files:\n- src/game/scriptlancer.ts — state machine, camera re-targeting, HUD show/hide\n- src/game/camera/chaseCamera.ts — purely functional, no changes expected; just swap the Object3D passed to updateChaseCamera\n- src/game/controls/flyByWire.ts — add input-disable flag or early-return guard\n- src/game/pilot/createAiPilot.ts — loiter mode when no target / target is dead\n- src/game/hud/* — visibility toggling during spectate\n\nValidation: vp check && vp test after implementation.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Death cam on player death: input disabled, HUD hidden, 1.2s smoothstep camera blend to enemy chase view, 15s spectate with reticle-styled overlay and click-to-respawn, AI wander-loiter, live bolt sim; instant snap back on respawn. flyByWire death-cam transition + snapChaseCameraToShip; bolt damage 10 HP. vp check && vp test pass.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-26T04:07:43.908Z","updated_at":"2026-06-26T05:11:18.078Z","started_at":"2026-06-26T04:44:36.649Z","completed_at":"2026-06-26T05:11:18.078Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
