{"id":"xw3fys60","parent_id":"0m493lgo","name":"LogTape logging: shared wrapper + server adoption","description":"Stand up structured logging with LogTape behind a thin shared wrapper, and adopt it on the server. First slice only -- client + sim deferred.\n\nGOAL: establish a single sanctioned logging path so we stop reaching for console.* directly. After this lands, console.log/console.error in app code is a smell -- use the shared logger unless it is absolutely necessary (e.g. user-facing CLI stdout in scripts/tools, or before logging is configured). This is the foundation the rest of the codebase migrates onto.\n\n1. SHARED WRAPPER (packages/shared/src/logging/): thin getLogger(category) returning a lowest-common-denominator interface -- debug/info/warn/error(message, fields?) + child(subcategory) -- that maps onto both LogTape and pino so the library can be swapped without touching callsites. Plus a configureLogging(sinks) helper centralizing category routing. shared never calls configure(). Unit-tested.\n\n2. SERVER ADOPTION (apps/server): call configure() once at startup; convert the four [server] console.* lines in index.ts to [scriptlancer,server,...] loggers.\n\nFORMATTERS/OUTPUT (https://logtape.org/manual/formatters): a sink (console/stream/file) and a formatter are separate choices. Dev = console sink + ansiColorFormatter (built-in, zero dep) OR @logtape/pretty prettyFormatter (nicer, extra package) -- pick one. Prod = console/stream sink + jsonLinesFormatter, which reliably serializes Error objects (matters for the error logging in step 2). jsonLinesFormatter properties option (flatten/nest/prefix) controls how the wrapper fields? render -- the seam for OTel later. Future: @logtape/redaction redactByPattern for masking session/connection data we log.\n\nDECISION: LogTape over pino -- cross-runtime monorepo, library-first design fits packages/shared, no prod hot-path logging, @logtape/otel covers ship-to-services-later. configure() is per-runtime and lives in each app entry, never in shared.\n\nCONVENTIONS: AGENTS.md -- @sideEffect on config/emit helpers, #/ imports with .ts suffix, type over interface.\n\nOUT OF SCOPE: client adoption, sim categories, OTel wiring (deferred); CLI one-offs (gen-cert.ts, bake-colliders) stay as user-facing stdout.","priority":1,"completed":false,"result":null,"metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-27T20:45:52.796Z","updated_at":"2026-06-27T21:00:11.160Z","started_at":null,"completed_at":null,"blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
{"id":"yc43t68n","parent_id":"2evkv6xf","name":"Phase 4 — Entity interpolation (remote ships)","description":"CONTEXT: Makes other players smooth despite 20Hz sends.\n\nINVESTIGATE: a per-remote snapshot buffer; rendering remotes ~100ms in the past; interpolating position and rotation (slerp) between buffered snapshots; handling missing/late/out-of-order packets and buffer underrun (brief extrapolation/dead-reckoning vs hold).\n\nOPEN QUESTIONS FOR THE USER: the interpolation delay value (start ~100ms, tune); extrapolate or freeze on starvation.\n\nREFERENCES (implement the standard pattern, do not invent one): Gabriel Gambetta \"Fast-Paced Multiplayer\" — Entity Interpolation https://www.gabrielgambetta.com/client-server-game-architecture.html\n\nDONE WHEN: remote ships move smoothly at display rate with no visible stepping at 20Hz snapshot rate.\n\nSTATUS (2026-06-29): Not started. The render interpolation added in PR #34 covers only the LOCAL predicted ship, which is a separate concern. Remote ships still snap to each snapshot (networkShipRegistry copies position and quaternion per snapshot, with no per-remote buffer, no ~100ms render delay, and no slerp between buffered snapshots). A reusable local-ship render-interpolation helper now exists and can inform the remote approach. Still blocks the networked-path half of consolidation (l2mowwvj).","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Remote-ship entity interpolation shipped and merged to main (PR feat/remote-entity-interpolation). Per-remote timestamped snapshot buffer in networkShipRegistry; new pure remoteInterpolation.ts (sampleRemoteBuffer) lerp/slerps between bracketing poses at a now-100ms render delay, freezes/holds on buffer underrun, drops reordered/duplicate datagrams by serverTick, and caps the buffer (MAX_REMOTE_SNAPSHOTS). updateRemotes() runs once per frame in createNetworkedScriptlancer. 8 unit tests; validation (vp check, tests, fallow) green. Verified live: two tabs side-by-side, both smooth, no 20Hz stepping.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-26T08:41:06.702Z","updated_at":"2026-06-29T23:27:19.649Z","started_at":"2026-06-29T22:42:59.845Z","completed_at":"2026-06-29T23:27:19.649Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":["l2mowwvj"],"children":[]}
