{"id":"z21uuc8d","parent_id":"ia40wzb6","name":"More global hotkeys (sidebar, workspaces, theme)","description":"GOAL\nExtend gdex keyboard shortcuts beyond the task list / task detail pane\n(completed in krkpzjdq). Add chrome-level hotkeys for sidebar toggle, workspace\ncycling, and theme mode. Quick-copy prompt shortcuts are explicitly out of scope\n(defer to a follow-up task).\n\nRELATIONSHIP TO PRIOR WORK\n- Branch `keys` (or merged main) already has task-board navigation: tinykeys\n  on `window`, `src/lib/keyboard/` (`keyBindings.ts`, `scope.ts`,\n  `taskListNavigation.ts`, `moveRepeat.ts`), hook\n  `src/hooks/useTaskListKeyboard.ts` wired from `WorkspaceMain`.\n- Existing guards: `checkIsEditableKeyboardTarget`,\n  `checkIsTargetInWorkspaceSidebar`, `checkIsTargetInNavigationScope`,\n  `checkHasAgentPromptMenu`. Task-list keys intentionally do not fire in the\n  sidebar or while typing in inputs.\n- New chrome shortcuts use Cmd-based bindings (see KEY BINDINGS). They must not\n  fight unmodified task-list keys (j/k/h/l, arrows, Backspace).\n\nKEY BINDINGS (macOS — document in `keyBindings.ts` using tinykeys notation)\n| Action              | Binding           | Notes                                      |\n| Toggle sidebar      | Cmd+B             | VS Code–style left panel toggle            |\n| Next workspace      | Cmd+Shift+]       | Wrap at end of registered workspace list   |\n| Previous workspace  | Cmd+Shift+[       | Wrap at start                              |\n| Cycle theme mode    | Cmd+Option+T      | light → dark → auto (same as top-bar btn)  |\n\nSCOPE RULES\n- Chrome shortcuts fire anytime the user is not typing in an editable target\n  (inputs, textarea, select, contenteditable) — same editable guard as today.\n- Unlike task-list nav, chrome shortcuts are NOT blocked when focus is in the\n  workspace sidebar or task list; user can collapse sidebar or switch workspace\n  from anywhere except text fields.\n- Block all chrome shortcuts while the agent prompt context menu is open\n  (`checkHasAgentPromptMenu`), matching existing menu guard patterns.\n- After workspace switch, task-list j/k/h/l navigation applies to the new\n  workspace with no extra reset.\n\nFEATURE AREAS\n\n1) Workspace sidebar expand/collapse\n- Today: `WorkspaceSidebar` keeps `isCollapsed` in local `useState`; toggle\n  via header control only.\n- Deliver: Cmd+B toggles collapsed strip ↔ expanded sidebar without clicking\n  the collapse control.\n- Lift collapse state (or expose a toggle action via store/context) so the\n  global keyboard hook can reach it.\n\n2) Cycle active workspace\n- Today: `useWorkspaceSelection` → `appStore.switchWorkspace` (with\n  transition). Sidebar lists workspaces; mouse picks one.\n- Deliver: Cmd+Shift+] / Cmd+Shift+[ move to next/previous workspace in the\n  registered list (wrap at ends), respecting `isWorkspaceSwitching` / errors\n  like the UI does.\n\n3) Theme mode (light / dark / auto)\n- Today: `appStore.cycleThemeMode` + `ThemeModeToggle` in `AppTopBar`\n  (`ThemeMode` in `src/schemas/theme.ts`).\n- Deliver: Cmd+Option+T cycles light → dark → auto (same order as top-bar).\n\nOUT OF SCOPE\n- Quick-copy prompt keyboard shortcuts (numbered slots, clipboard feedback).\n- Command palette, arbitrary rebinding UI, cheatsheet overlay.\n- AGENTS.md shortcut cheat sheet unless the human asks.\n\nCODEBASE STARTING POINTS\n- Repo: gdex (Tauri + Preact). Read `AGENTS.md` for conventions (Bun, `@/`\n  imports, naming, validation loop).\n- Keyboard: extend `src/lib/keyboard/keyBindings.ts` + handler wiring. Prefer one\n  window-level hook (e.g. unified `useWindowKeyboard` in `WorkspacesLayout`)\n  with a single tinykeys subscription — refactor task-list wiring into it rather\n  than adding a second listener.\n- Store: `src/stores/appStore.ts` (`switchWorkspace`, `cycleThemeMode`,\n  workspaces, `activeWorkspaceId`; consider sidebar collapsed state here).\n- Sidebar: `src/components/WorkspaceSidebar/`, `data-workspace-sidebar` in\n  `scope.ts`.\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n- Sidebar toggle, workspace prev/next, and theme cycle work end-to-end in the\n  desktop app without mouse.\n- Bindings match the KEY BINDINGS table above (encoded in `keyBindings.ts`).\n- Shortcuts do not break task-list j/k/h/l navigation or fire during text entry.\n- `bun run check`, `typecheck`, `test`, `fallow:audit` pass (same bar as\n  krkpzjdq).\n- Brief result note confirming bindings and scope rules (editable + menu guards).\n\nSUGGESTED APPROACH\n- Add chrome actions to `keyBindings.ts` (or sibling module if it grows).\n- Centralize `checkShouldHandleChromeShortcut` (or similar) next to `scope.ts`\n  helpers — editable target + agent prompt menu; do NOT reuse sidebar exclusion\n  from task-list guards.\n- Pure helpers + tests for workspace prev/next index math (wrap at ends).\n- Smoke-test sidebar toggle, workspace cycle, and theme in the desktop app.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Global chrome shortcuts: ⌘B sidebar, ⌘⇧]/[ workspace cycle, ⌘⌥T theme. Keyboard shortcuts section added to README.md.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-04T08:35:45.359Z","updated_at":"2026-06-06T19:32:40.561Z","started_at":"2026-06-06T18:39:32.341Z","completed_at":"2026-06-06T19:32:40.561Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
{"id":"z3ksyi5w","parent_id":"jvprxjqg","name":"Import: confirm before DB + Spoonacular","description":"## Goal\nSingle commit path after human confirm. **Zero** DB writes and **zero** Spoonacular/Claude enrichment during scan.\n\n## Why (read parent `jvprxjqg`)\nTurso should only receive imports Greg has audited. Spoonacular + Claude candidate-pick are expensive and pointless if the parse is wrong — run them **only after confirm**, for ingredients actually being saved.\n\n## Today\n- Scan: `resolveIngredientsAgainstDb` inserts `ingredient` rows + may Spoonacular-enrich (`ingredient-resolution.ts`).\n- Confirm-ish: **Create recipe** already inserts `recipe` + `recipe_ingredient` only (but ingredient IDs must already exist from scan).\n- Escape hatch: manual enrich on `/ingredient` list stays.\n\n## Work\n1. Scan/extract: structured preview only; optional **read-only** match to existing ingredients for display labels (no insert).\n2. Confirm: resolve/create ingredients → Spoonacular for **new** rows only (if key set) → insert recipe + joins; one server fn / transaction preferred.\n3. UI: confirm vs discard; drop “new ingredient” badges that implied DB state during scan.\n4. **If Greg flags a bad site during this work:** stop coding around it — capture URL + HTML fixture under `test/fixtures/recipes/golden/`, adjust prompts/schemas, run `bun run test:ai:recipe:url:golden`. Collaborate; don’t auto-insert workarounds.\n\n## Acceptance\n- `ingredient` row count unchanged after scan, before confirm.\n- Spoonacular not called during scan.\n- After confirm: same end state as today when key present.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Merged PR #5: preview-only extract, confirm-time resolve + Spoonacular, duplicate URL check, transactional persist (ingredient match + recipe insert).","metadata":{"commit":{"sha":"dc3a359","message":":rabbit: more coderabbit feedback","branch":"main","timestamp":"2026-05-18T05:37:06.618Z"}},"created_at":"2026-05-18T04:18:44.556Z","updated