{"id":"zu5cxe3q","parent_id":"2evkv6xf","name":"Phase 0 — Fixed-timestep refactor: split sim from render","description":"CONTEXT: Current loop (src/game/scriptlancer.ts:409) steps Rapier once per render frame with variable dt — non-deterministic and incompatible with netcode. This phase is the foundation everything else rides on.\n\nINVESTIGATE: the accumulator pattern (while (acc >= TICK) step(TICK)); how flightControls, playerShipPhysics, aiPilot, weaponSystem, effects, and camera are currently coupled in the one loop; render-time interpolation of transforms between the last two sim states; the existing MAX_FRAME_SECONDS clamp.\n\nOPEN QUESTIONS FOR THE USER: confirm 60Hz sim tick; how much visual change (if any) is acceptable during the cutover.\n\nREFERENCES (follow the standard pattern, do not invent one): Glenn Fiedler / Gaffer On Games \"Fix Your Timestep!\" https://gafferongames.com/post/fix_your_timestep/\n\nDONE WHEN: sim runs on a fixed 60Hz accumulator, render interpolates at display rate, flight feels unchanged, and a recorded input sequence reproduces identical state across runs.","priority":1,"completed":true,"result":"Fixed-timestep refactor: 60Hz accumulator sim split from display-rate render, with saveSimState/syncInterpolated interpolation (nlerp + dot-sign guard). Flight feel unchanged; determinism test added. Merged via PR #23.","metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-06-26T08:41:06.182Z","updated_at":"2026-06-27T04:01:52.318Z","started_at":"2026-06-26T20:19:44.546Z","completed_at":"2026-06-27T04:01:52.318Z","blockedBy":[],"blocks":[],"children":[]}
